1. create github acct for project
2. install and configure nodemailer (send mails)
3. push code to github and deploy
4. install and configure react-quill (upload and edit blogs)
5. restrict the blog/upload route from 3rd parties through the use of login
6. on the homepage the blog section fetches only the latest 3 upload from the backend and displays them.

- you could do something like, Array.sort() - sort by date created in ascending order

7. clicking on one of the blog item on the homepage navigates the user to the route blog/:id where id is what uniquely identifies the clicked blog
